The only negative was the handle.  Other reviewers had mentioned this, but it only extends to super high...it doesn't seem to stay clicked at the more reasonable mid-level...so be careful not to take out too many people when running from gate-to-gate.  I preferred to keep it in front of me and push to avoid unnecessary contact with others and/or toppling items when perusing the duty-free store.

I let myself get carried away with the cuteness of this bag, a mistake. Pros: it does seem like it's going to be extremely durable, even if you are like me and wheel your suitcase many miles on uneven surfaces. if you pack it cleverly, it will hold quite a lot while still being able to squeeze it into most overhead bins (not on the small planes though, and not if you have the expansion compartment open). I LOVE that it has only two wheels, which can be removed and replaced easily with an allen wrench -- something very hard to find.

Cons:
1. The handle defaults to the longest length (which is VERY long), terrible for crowds. if you want it to be a normal length, you have to stop and push the handle back down before you go every single time. very inconvenient if you are trying to get going and out of the way as quickly as possible.

2. the "main" compartment is quite shallow, so about about 1/3 of the capacity is in the outside pocket. personally I prefer my suitcases to be deep like a trunk and I save the outside for very slim things, like a laptop. to make matters worse, the interior space between the two bars is filled in. that eliminates even more space that efficient packers might use. (one pro: the suitcase will not tip over on carpet when totally full.)

3. with my old suitcase, I preferred to prop the lid against the wall and drop small things into the mesh pocket. on this model, the zipper is on the wrong side so if you want to use that compartment, you have to keep the lid flat on the floor. seems minor, but really bothered me.

minor things: the tough shell has been warped outwards on the right after carrying it around by the side handle. also the smallest pockets on the outside are barely accessable -- it's hard to squeeze your hand into them. I only use them for tiny things that I rarely need access to, so those pockets seem pretty unnecassary and add bulk to the interior. these details are not a huge deal, but just a bunch of little things that added up.

I just took my new suitcase on a trip to the Turks and Caicos. I couldn't believe how much lighter it was than my Travel Pro! It holds the same amount with much less weight. It has nice features that helps with packing. I chose green to make it easy to spot amongst the sea of black on the carousel. I wish I had dumped my Travel Pro in favor of this years ago.

Dunno how I lived without this product...it's really a great invention! This loops through your belt and acts as another belt loop. I clip my keys and a waterbottle to it for hands-free work, and it takes the stress off of the loops and onto the belt. It works with gun belts, but might be a bit tight. Also to note, the edges and corners are slightly sharp and may cut into whatever you sit on, I would recommend grinding or sanding it down to make it smooth.

Clip JUST fits over my 1.25" belt. Very snug, but it does fit. I cannot see it fitting on anything bigger at all. I've only had this a little while so I can't speak to the longevity, but I don't see why it would break down too quickly. The overall action of sliding a key ring on/off isn't as smooth and mindless as I would like. I'm not saying it's bad, but I've had other holders that are much easier. There are mini ridges cut into the stainless laterally to give the swing-arm a bit of texture. I'm not sure what it's there for other than decoration, but they slow the movement down just a bit. In addition, the area that you must press the swing-arm in order to remove a key ring is very small and it seems like your thumb is just in the way.

The biggest problem I have is the manufacturing. The metal eems like it was rough-cut out of a bigger sheet but no effort was made to smooth the edges. If you take the holder and moderately brush it against your skin, it'll rough it up leaving white makes, but not drawing any blood. It's not sharp enough to cut your skin or even snag clothing, but the edges are clearly not smooth. This won't be an issue for causal users, but for those with there hands on it 24/7, it'll get annoying. I don't use mine much, I just need to keep keys out of my pocket, so I'm going to use this. However, for heavy users, I'd sped a few more dollars and get a finished product.

reviewText:
I am writing this two months after receiving the item.  I bought this for my wife for our fifth anniversary. An almost exact version is sold at Sam's Club for over $400 more.  She loved it right out of the box.  It appears well made.

PROS:

- Price was the best I could find
- Settings seem good - no diamonds lost yet!
- White gold beats silver and so pendant hasn't turned colors. Note chain is silver.
- Size was about what I expected - but I always remember that jewelry is not as big as it is on the screen.*
- Chain is okay(functional), but at some point it is always better to buy a stronger thick chain (white gold) for your loved one's jewelry.
- Nice box; well packaged - always important when giving jewelry as a gift.
- Delivered in a reasonable time

CONS (from mine not my wife's perspective):

- Needs good lighting for diamonds to sparkle*
- Though setting seems well made, reflection of diamonds not as bright as I'd like*
  Rating of 3.5/4 given due to this.

*Notes: Convert MM to Inches and get out the ruler so you know the size you are getting.
  It seems that clarity ratings/cloudiness are nearly always low for pendants (here or at other online stores).

OVERALL: This item works for value, as comparable items I have seen are about the same quality. My wife is happy with it and that's what really matters.  I am a little more critical when spending money on jewelry since jewelry is a very high-profit item.  Sam's Club had these on sale at the store at the time of this review, may want to check theirs out or a jewelry store for comparison (compare by clarity ratings).  My unofficial non-numeric ratings: COLOR -  slightly off-clear; CUT -  Fair (affects brightness); Clarity - some minor defects.
summary: GREAT VALUE - WELL MADE - CLARITY SO-SO

reviewText: Lymphoma took my Dad's life in 2010. I have supported the research of finding a cure for this miserable disease. When I came across this bracelet, I had to try it and see. A big selling point for me was that a portion of the sale will be donated to the American Cancer Society. They need all the extra funds possible. Delivery was very fast. The bracelet came in on a card, wrapped in clear plastic. You could certainly gift this item as is upon delivery. On the back of the card it was on, there is a huge list of different cancers and what color is associated with that cancer. Makes me wonder, who came up with the coloring? The bracelet itself is very pretty. Nice quality. The beads are separated with silver beads and silver, daisy spacers.. The seller stated there are two extension rings to offer larger siz, but my bracelet actually came with three rings. There is also a little, silver cancer ribbon on the bracelet. I really don't see that detail lasting very long...but this bracelet is just a little something for me. So it really doesn't matter much. I would recommend this item and the seller. I did receive this item at a discount in return for my honest review. I was not guided on what to write nor was I compensated. 100% honest.

I'm well within, actually on the small side, for the size I ordered. I almost got a hernia getting one leg in, up to the thigh and gave up. There was no point in trying to get both legs in, it would've just been painful. The other strange thing about these tights (and I do mean TIGHTS) is the toe. The toe and heel are made from a different material than the tights, which would be really nice, but there's a seam and it's not in the front or on the top, where you'd expect it. The seam is under the toes, which would just make it annoying and uncomfortable. You can't just turn it over, either because of the specified heel. Sad to say, but I'm returning these.
Definitely NOT what is suggested, maybe compression tights for a toddler!

If you're looking for compression tights, Preggers are the best.  I wish I discovered these in my pregnancy but I certainly need them more in my second, where I feel like if I don't wear them, I need to lift my belly.  These are expensive and I do find they run moreso than regular non-maternity tights but let's face it, they get worn a lot harder.  I also find it, especially now in my 3rd trimester, irreplaceable and a necessary.  It's my goal to find them cheaper since I refuse to live without them!  They are pretty challenging to get on but the reward is after you put them on.  I would give these as shower gifts to other moms--that's how awesome they are.
summary: Best Maternity Compression Tights out there

reviewText: A must for a pregnant wan who wears tights

I am pretty short, so I ordered the petite plus based on the size chart.  I hit about the middle of the weight zone for that size, so I expected them to fit well.  However, when I took them out of the package, they were about 5" wide and tightly woven, with no additional front panel.  The company clearly has higher expectations of a pregnant woman's ability to get her knee up to her chin while using herculean strength to stretch out the waist to order to get your foot in.  I was out of breath and frustrated, and feeling a bit trapped when I did get them on.  They are already charging several times the cost of normal tights so I feel ripped off!
summary: You might have better chances wrestling a bear than getting in these tights!

Excerpt from:  HISTORY OF THE UNITED STATES FLAG - CALIFORNIA BEAR FLAG
"... Needing an emblem for their cause, the men hunted about for materials from which to make a flag.  Some white cotton was obtained for the field, and along its bottom edge was sewn a four-inch-wide strip of red flannel.  A young man named William L. Todd, cousin to Mary Todd Lincoln, drew on its field designs suggested by the company.  First came that traditional American emblem of independent Statehood, a single star, reminiscent of the Lone Star of Texas.  Todd colored it in with red paint made (according to the best available contemporary description) from `blackberry juice, brick dust, and oil.'  Facing the star he also painted in red a crude representation of a grizzly bear standing on all fours.  Beneath the star and the bear were outlined in black the words CALIFORNIA REPUBLIC. ..."

Now you have a description of the 1846 California National Flag (aka California Bear Flag).

Before I placed my order, I gave the company a call to verify the colors (mainly that the stripe, bear and star were in fact red in color).  They stated that they were and that the lettering was dark brown and not black, but appeared black unless viewed within a few inches.  So, I placed my order for the shirt.

Upon receiving the shirt, the shirt was not white in color (as even the picture shows) but beige (reminiscent of those old hemp t-shirts).  The stripe, star, and bear are not red in color, but dark brown.

The product and customer service for this item are an EPIC FAIL.  I rate them -1000 stars.

I like nice things, and this bag is definately nice.  Looks well constructed; zipper seems sturdy.  The interior has a small zippered slot in the lid...maybe to store your meds separately from larger items.  Lots of space in the main compartment for mouthwash, shaving cream, brush, razor, floss, etc.  The bag profile is low, so stowed items shouldn't shift around much.  My only beefs are:  I was hoping for the high price for such an item that it would be made in the USA -- not so; DomRepublic.  So, even though it's made of leather, the price is too high.  Since I like it and I'm preparing to travel overseas, I'm going to keep it regardless of the price.  My second beef is, the bag has a 5-year warranty, but the warranty does NOT cover damage resulting from NORMAL WEAR (emphasis is mine).  Does this company expect the owner to keep this bag in a drawer for five years and not use it?  Oh well, as with most of the warranty cards that come with products I buy, I toss them in the garbage to prevent future aggravation.  Bottom line:  the bag is nice and functional, but there are probably just-as-good bags on the market for a lower price.  I know I'll enjoy it.  If something bad happens to this bag during my overseas trip, I'll provide an update.

The flash worked great and I'm very happy with my purchase.

I have been seeking a ring light for photographing display models (aircraft, cars, etc) for a number of years as I wanted to eliminate directional shadows from "normal" flash units. Nothing available was of sufficient diameter to meet my needs so I "cobbled up" an automotive halo powered by a motorcycle battery (made a shoulder sling for the battery) that was half a solution as it did not provide enough light for indoor lighting needs.

While searching for other photographic items, I saw this unit in the list of other items on the Amazon search page. I was skeptical (too much experience with failed products) but elected to give it a try. Bought it and received it Aug 18th, did some test shots of my own models and was satisfied that it would do the job I needed, specifically, that I am the "designated" photographer for some of our models shows. Note that this unit will work either as a continuous light, adjustable for brightness, or as a flash that provides 2x the output of the "continuous" setting. Sometimes continuous produces better results, sometimes flash is better. I habitually check the view screen and switch or adjust output if a reshoot is needed. Note also that the power is provided by four AA batteries; I expected to have to change them often as I've found I have to do with my standard flash units that are good for about 120-150 shots. So, two months later, what is my experience?

In September, I covered a model show for which I took nearly 700 shots with this ring flash. This is the fourth time I've covered that annual show, the first two times with hot-shoe flashes, the third time with my halo/motorcycle battery lash-up, and this year with this ring light. The photos taken with the ring light are much more consistent and of far better "lighting" quality than those of the preceding years. An affirmation to me is that one of the club officers commented that the photos were much better "this year" than before.

I've also taken nearly 200 shots of my own models and for other tests (still life, flowers, and detail photos of 1:1 car engine modifications). Occasionally, I've had to reset output or switch from continuous to flash or vice versa, but, overall, estimate a maximum of 5% reshoots. And, to my amazement and appreciation, I still have the original four AA batteries in the unit.

Is there a downside? I have used it exclusively on a Canon 18-200 zoom and the adapter to mount the unit vignettes at wider zoom settings. Vignetting, of course, will vary with the lens used so that is a minimal "downside" in my opinion. Other than that, I find this unit to be better than expected and as good as what I hoped to have for many a year.

Opinion: The ring light offer includes a "Free Floureon Card Reader" which is a USB2 device. As I was an early adopter of USB3, the card reader is, to me, a superfluous "bonus" that I have not used; other buyers might find it useful.
summary: Two months after buying, used for nearly 1000 photos, VERY pleased!

reviewText:
I was a fan of their Slim Sleeve wallet even though the first one I got had some definitely quality issue but the subsequent one was better, but not perfect, with varying degree of imperfections but as I've been told, it is part of their "personality".

When I lost my wallet and saw they came out with the Note Sleeve I was ecstatic, ordered it right away, since the whole bill folding was an annoyance. The card sleeve and quick access slots are definitely the major selling points of this product for me. I've found the SIM card slot useful also for international travel but those with iPhones will need a full size SIM adapter in order for it to work.

I've had this wallet for over a year now and visually it has not held up too well. According to their site this is expected " develop a patina quickly, showing marks, usage and character much sooner", but still surprising how terrible it looks compared to a wallet half the price. Some people call it character, but to me it ends up making it look much older and worn than it really is.

The main gripe about this wallet is which I think makes it almost pointless to choose over the Slim Sleeve, is that the note compartment is just barley enough to fit bills. Like one of the previous reviewer says, they have to be perfectly aligned or you just end up with a mess, quite a hassle especially when you are trying to quickly shove your change back into the wallet and move out of the way. I find this makes it no better than folding the bills.
summary: Overpriced and the most distinguishing feature is flawed

reviewText: The wallet is definitely slim, but maybe too slim for my taste. As the wallet breaks in you can see distinct lines from the edges of all cards and even the edges of a bill that has a corner folded over. The design is really nice with the three commonly used card slots, and a pullout tab for you less used (stacked) cards; but again the leather on the outside shows the outline of the pullout tab. Overall I'm happy with it, but for the price I would like to see slightly thicker leather to hide the outlines of the contents.
summary: Breaking it in shows its true form

reviewText:
This is a decent wallet.  It's not even close to worth the price though.

The leather quality isn't anything extraordinary - as they claim.  The leather is already showing signs of wear after 4 months of everyday use.  The craftsmanship is decent provided it passes quality control.  Upon receipt, I had to send back the first one I received for a replacement because a cut in the leather was made too far.  Bellroy customer service wasn't good. They provided the bare minimum from what I'd expect from a higher end manufacturer.

Paper bills need to be perfectly aligned in order to slide cleanly into the wallet - difficult if you have 5 or more bills.

The pull tab is a piece of leather that has already stretched past it's original length.  Again, everyday use.  The pull tab is cheaply made.  If it were two pieces stitched together, it may prevent this from happening?

I expect this wallet to last maybe 2 years.  On the plus side, it has forced me to reduce the amount of stuff that I've put in my wallet (compared to past wallets).

From Bellroy's ads, I thought I would end up with a super-thin wallet.  The high price suggested that it might be magic.  However, it wasn't magic.  Nice wallet, but no thinner than the one I already had.  I returned it and got my money back.

Good quality material and is exactly what I was looking for. The leather isn't stiff at all and is very flexible and slim. I can easily get my IDs out with one hand while driving. Fits in to pockets easily and doesn't get stuck
Its a great wallet but I needed sometime to get used to the size but now I'm loving  it. worthy
THis is a very good product. It was shipped quickly as well. I would give it a 5 but it is kinda bulky when i  put my cards in it. But it may be that i have to many cards.
I really have enjoyed this wallet - Bellroy has figured out one of man's age old problems. This wallet has literally decreased a pain in the rear. Great design and high quality!

I purchased mine direct from Bellroy. The wallet is extremely thin as promised, but has enough features to be useful. for more than just carrying a few cards. It holds more than I thought it would when I ordered it. No problems with the leather pull tab that I've read others had issues with. My old wallet wasn't a Costanza wallet, but it was thick with nothing in it so this is a very pleasant change. The flap and pocket for business cards and coins is nice. There is an extra slot in the bill area for another card which could be used for my driver's license, though I prefer keeping it in the stack of cards to keep the wallet slim.

The leather appears to be good quality (only had for a week, so durability not known). It's not so thin that it will scratch easily and contrary to what I read elsewhere, it will hold more than 5 bills and will not show a folded corner of the bill through the leather. It does show the edges of my cards through the leather however, but that doesn't bother me.

All in all, I am very pleased with this product.

reviewText: Keeps you warm at a low cost, well worth the money, great size and doesn't make your nose itchy .

I bought this to supplement the rest of the cold weather gear that I wear while working. I spend a portion of each work day inside of a walk in freezer that is set to -10 degrees. Wearing a hoodie, jacket, snowboard gloves and a balaclava wasn't enough to keep me from getting cold in that environment. After getting this and wearing it the first day, I was amazed at how much of difference this thing could make.

I wear this wrapped twice around my neck like a wrap underneath my hoody. With the other items, it's kept me warm enough that I don't need to wear a coat if I know I'll be be spending less than 10 minutes in the freezer. (As long as I wear the hoodie.) Because it's made of fleece, it doesn't suffer from the same heat loss you might get from knit scarves. I think it comes in other colors than orange, but I like orange so it suits me well.

the chain broke on the first day of wear. It's a severely over-priced item for the quality you get. 15.00 for some simple looking hand painted seahorse on a simple chain that breaks in hours?

reviewText: I like it very much, hope you guys make a bigger version of it.

'OMG' - Is that not what the kids say these days?
My little princess, now four, is SO in love with this thing. It is just wonderful to observe how much she enjoys this.  On the couch, on the floor, in bed, grandma's, in her chair reading, everywhere.
Material is that nice, soft bath towel feel. Stitching has held together after, at least, 30+ washes. Colors have held up.  Her face just positively beams when put on right out-of-the-dryer...
Little crown on top is just so cute.
My daughter will wear to bed and use in lieu of covers. (we put her in very light pajamas, and she wraps herself in poncho)
Here is where you must be CAREFUL-
There are TWO of these versions out there- exactly the same except the LENGTH.
DO NOT SCREW UP and buy the shorter one. (Will be a major disappointment)
Ensure to buy the LONGER one which goes down to your kids knees. (Don't worry- even though it is longer, there is no problem going up/down the stairs)
I can not emphasize how much of a difference the length makes. (We tried to buy a second one and did not catch it was the short version.)  The shorter one cuts to mid-back and does not allow for the 'wrapped-up, warm, snug-as-a-bug, comfort, security' feeling.  Our (same) kid shunned it. Boy, did we get an education. So, back it went.
Other than the length, you simply can not go wrong with this thing. After a sleep-over, all the other parents hit us with 'Where did you buy that? (!)'  My kid won't stop talking about (bugging me to buy one) it.
Little unhappy about the higher price, but with all things Disney, you gotta pay the extra $.  Very happy with this purchase.
summary: Poncho Princess blanket:  TWO VERSIONS- BE CAREFUL and get the correct one

reviewText:
I received this as a gift for Christmas this past year from my mother-in-law...I know...great stuff! Coach bags are close to the top of my list on my favorite designer handbags. What is unique about this purse is that it has what I call a racing stripe down the middle. At first I was really not that fond of the stripe down the middle and to be honest it is still growing on me...hence the 4 stars.

Some of the features that I love are:
-An open outer pocket that can fit my keys and cell phone. It is very handy and helps you avoid the whole digging through the bottom of your purse thing!
-It is really roomy inside without being or looking bulky. I am a wife and mom and my purses need to carry some heavy duty things around with it. I was able to fit my large wallet, large water bottle, 2 glasses cases, hand sanitize, cosmetics, snacks, etc. with complete ease.
-Versatile compartments. It has 2 inner pockets and both are great sizes to fit toiletry items and more.

The feel and sturdiness of this purse is amazing. I guarantee that almost anyone will be happy with this purse.

But I find that it stretches somewhat throughout the day so it is definitely a little forgiving for me. Also, because it has that looser cut in the front, it does not accentuate my middle section as much as some others. I love love love that the sleeves are longer, too. reviewText: WONDERFUL QUALITY, GREAT COLOR. COMES WITH PROTECTIVE BAG TO STORE IT, JUST LIKE A COACH PURSE WOULD.  TON'S OF ROOM WITH 1 INTERIOR ZIPPERED POCKET AND 2 INTERIOR OPEN POCKETS ALSO.

I have been looking for a cross body bag (with removable short handles) for a long time.  This one fit the bill for me.  It is attractive, looks just like pictured, the interior lining is leopard print, nice accent.  I use it on my commute to work and it fits everything I bring, my lunch, book, phone, wallet, gloves, etc.  Because it is vinyl it is a bit heavy when it is fully packed.  The pockets in and out are convenient for easy access and security.  My biggest complaint is the outside wide zipper pocket, it is very shallow and actually quite useless, you can store pens, a comb, small items.  Had that pocket been deeper you would be able to store the book or gloves for easy access.

I have only used it one day but I noticed when I unpacked it that the main zipper was a bit touchy so I'm hoping it holds up.  If not, I will let you know.  Otherwise, it is the perfect size and color and I especially love the fact that it does NOT have a center divider pocket.

Take this review with a grain of salt because I purchased this tote/purse/etc. for my g/f. I purchased this purse because it met her criteria: zipped top, at least one outside pocket, and shoulder strap.

Purse seems well made and has ample room if you're looking for a larger bag. It can easily hold a 10 inch iPad along with all your other necessities.

My only gripe with this purse is the inside organization. Sure it has one inside zipped pocket, and three pockets on the other side, but it would be nice if there was a divider zipped pocket pocket in the middle of the bag for better organization. If you're in to the cheetah print, you'll be happy to find that in this purse. However, the fabric they used for the interior feels kind of cheap, but I guess you can't have it all in this price range.

Another feature of this bag is that the top handles are on clips, so they easily fall to the sides of the bag if you're using the shoulder strap. Because the the handles are on clips they are also removable. If you find them too short, you can easily replace them or use metal rings or something to make them longer.

The long zipper on the outside can easily hold a pair of sunglasses, cell phone, etc. The smaller outside pocket is really only usable for a cell phone or something flat in that nature.

I purchased this bag in gray and my g/f is really happy with the color. The tassels are a nice addition as the bag is rather plain looking.

2/16/15 Update:

Yes, it does look like a temp tatt but it is VERY detailed and the definition extends all the way down to the small feathers. Nice piece of art work on it's own.

Application was very easy, taking less than 5 minutes. Once on it looked good but just not me. I kept it for a few days to get use to it. About a week later I was tired of it and very glad it was not permanent, well at least not easy to get rid of.

Removal was the very opposite of application. The instructions were simple enough, scrub with alcohol until gone. This procedure cost me half a bag of cotton balls and a quarter bottle of rubbing alcohol and 3 layers of skin. Point I'm laboring to make is, once on it ain't coming off without a little help.

Buy again? For me no, but I've got kiddos that would love smaller versions.

reviewText: We previously owned Momo soft sole slippers (Momo Baby Infant/Toddler Rainbow Lily Soft Sole Leather Shoes) which worked well for us. However, these are a different style, cut like a mary jane shoe. The elastic is tight and pulls the strap at an odd angle. The toes are very wide, leaving them gaping and looking awkward on my toddler's feet. If I were to order another pair, I would go back to the other style of slipper.

My baby was 10 months when we bought these and she's a cute chunky baby with barely an ankle, lol. I feel as though the top of the shoe and the stretchy elastic around the back of the ankle were too tight. I would not recommend this shoe to a baby with chubby feet. Definitely needs to be a skinny long foot for these. It just cut off her circulation in my opinion. Although, like I said, very cute and they never fell off, and walking in them didn't seem to bother her.
summary: A little too snug for my little one.

reviewText: Super cute shoes that fit well. Appear to be comfy for my little one.

Within a week, the leather began to crack and wear off. Within a couple of months the backs of the shoes showed cracking and paint was coming off. Really disappointing. Save yourself the trouble and spend a few bucks more for a different brand that actually maintains its quality.
summary: Not worth the money at all

reviewText: Love them!

Great crib shoe, and good for a little one first learning to walk. They have a soft sole that is suede to prevent slipping, which is especially handy for new walkers, and they are light weight so they don't discourage walking. They get your little one accustomed to shoes while protecting their feet. My son wore these for about two months before his first 'real' shoes and they held up to his walking/toddling/falling/crawling well and made switching to actual shoes a breeze. They are a little snug at first (like all shoes you need to break them in) but easily should fit most babies. At about 12 months you'll want to transition to a sturdier shoe anyhow so the size ranges shouldn't be a problem.

If your baby has NBA player sized feet and you're worried the weight of an actual shoe will discourage walking but these are much too snug, I've found sandals to be a good alternative. They'll protect the foot, aren't too heavy, and babies are cute enough to pull off wearing them with socks still. lol.
They were okay. Fit was fine, easy to put on, baby didn't seem restricted, but he is pretty hard on shoes and we do a lot outdoors. They scuff up pretty easy.
I love these! My only complaint is that the elastic seems pretty tight and leaves marks, but maybe that's just because my kid is chubby :P
So cute!! My son wore these constantly!! Great for new walkers.

Many of the regular shoes with thick soles are too firm to all him to walk, but these are perfect. He tore them up a bit in the toe by crawling a little on cement. I had his foot measured at a shoe store before I ordered and they said he was a size 4. I ordered the 4.5-5.5 12-18 month size, but there is not a lot of room to grow. You may want to order up a size.

Characters are well developed and tells the story of Canada's role in the war through the eyes of the women who worked in a munitions factory.  I'm hooked.  I feel like I just discovered the next Downton Abby-like sleeper.

This show was a big surprise for me.... I DVRd it and it sat on my DVR for a year... finished watching all my normal Chick shows, parenthood, nurse jackie,  nashville, and greys anatomy, I finally had sometime and watched the first episode of Bomb Girls while my baby napped. The 'Jasmine' purse cover is one of my favorites. (The company calls it a shell, because it's the outer layer of the purse, but I'll call it a cover for those who don't know about this product.)

I love the whole look of this cover. I love the style and the colors. I bought it from my representatives' online store. I haven't bought one from amazon yet, but if I find one that's cheaper than the ones that are sold on the Miche website, I might buy it.

The covers are held on by magnets. There are magnets on the base bag as well as on the cover. So you won't have to worry about them falling off. The picture for this product shows the whole bag with the cover on it, but each one is sold separately. The base bag is all black, but the covers can come in all kinds of different colors. The covers are also made with different materials. Some of the covers are made from fabric, and some aren't.

I chose the Miche bag because I have different clothing tastes and I like to mix or match what I wear with what purse cover I use. I can wear purple & black and use a purple cover for my purse, or I can wear blue and use a blue purse cover, or I can mix things up a little bit and instead of using a blue purse cover with a blue shirt, I can use my black purse cover while wearing my blue shirt. Black looks good with any color. It looks good with red, purple, blue, pink, white, green, gray, turquoise, teal,.. anything. With the Miche bag, there are endless possibilities.

The bra area has a tiny little padding inserted into it, which is in no way or shape a "push up", and it was rolled up and I couldn't unroll them to be flat on my chest.  Also, there is SO much material on the chest area, when my husband opened up the chest piece against my body, they went all the way to my arms.  (There is no elastic that allows the suit to hug your body, and the material is definitely not the tight swimsuit material, the only thing that holds the suit to your body are the strings that tie behind your neck & back.)  There is even too much material around the belly, I think, and let's just say, I do not have a six pack, and have plenty left over from having kids.
